Text: John Last night I towed my boat from a storage unit near Lake Conroe to a new one on just east of I which is a little more convenient I think the best thing for my trailer is to back it into a fresh water lake after it has been is salt water That way the salt water will be rinsed out of the interior of the trailer What do you think Also if we go what time would you want to head out Scott Jacobucci PE Principal Operations Engineer El Paso Merchant Energy office cell This email and any files transmitted with it from the ElPaso Corporation are confidential and intended solely for the use of the individual or entity to whom they are addressed If you have received this email in error please notify the sender
